title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1973-09-07
lineage: AUDMC (AKG 1000 mic > Sony 110 deck. ) > DAT > CD > EAC > SHN
description: Promised Land, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, They Love Each Other, Jack Straw, Looks Like Rain, Deal, El Paso, Bird Song, Playin' In The Band Here Comes Sunshine, Me & My Uncle, Loser, Let It Grow-> Stella Blue, Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Eyes Of The World-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Around & Around

reviews.review_text:
Now that we can only download audience recordings, I have started checking out a lot more obscure audience recordings ,and I have been very happy with a lot of shows I would've passed up when the SBD's were up for us.This show is real nice and I think that it captures the essence of the show better than the board.I really like '73 and to me the second half of '73 they were on fireSBD's from this era ,IMO The drums are almost always too loud in the mix and Jerry's too low.A few other AUD's I would recommend is 7/1/73,5/8/77,12/30/78,,1/10-11/79,
1/15/79,2/3/79,9/6/80,,12/13/80,3/24/90.I could go on ,because there is an endless well of great AUD's out there and on here.When I first started trading tapes it was 25 years ago and you had to go out there and find 'em yourself ,and then you had to tape each show in real time.There was no click a  link and   'bam you got 20 shows in one day.It was take what you can get that was decent quality.An AUD that has not been thru tape generations has great potential to be very nice,so dont be upset that we can't get SBD's here anymore, cause if you want 'em they are out there.I really love this site and love induldging myself with ease ,but it used to be ritualistic trading tapes, and since there was so much work getting them ,you really cherished your collection.If you lost one ,you may never get it again ,or so it seemed until the past few years.I give this show 5 stars even tho the quality is not the best .It has a good vibe and is very listenable.
Get it rick says it all.  he has the right idea and this is truly a great recording.

This one is the bomb Really... if you haven't heard 9/7/73 you have been missing one of the great shows of 73.  My personal favorite of all shows.  Really.  There was never a more powerful Here Comes Sunshine than this one, believe me, I've searched.  And the Eyes is powerful too.  A great audience recording of the boys at their absolute best.

great aud- under reviewed show that should be heard hard to believe this is an aud with the instrument separations being near perfect- birdsong is outstanding- top ten in my book- give it a listen- you will be surprised and you will download it for sure

good quality aud with blemishes i have to say that this is a decent quality aud.  it's slow to start.  that's either a factor of the band tuning the sound system in, or the taper getting dialed, or both.  i'm guessing the latter.  by row jimmy, the sound is fabulous despite the lunk heads who call for "me and my uncle" over and over.  (they're the reason i used to move around so much at shows -- trying to find a good "zone").

a bird song fan, i was tantalized by the previous review.  however, jerry's equipment problems (bob's been making some sly, cryptic equipment remarks all along) fuzz out and dump static where he should be sublimely lifting off.  if you're in search of the sublime bird song aud, check out 6-22-73.  other than that, it's hard to compete with 8-27-72.

for reason of equipment problems, thus far, i can't go above four stars, and that's feeling generous.  this is more like a 3.5.  here comes sunshine is good, but there are others that meet and exceed this version.  definitely worth a listen, though, especially the 2nd sent jam.  the first let it grow is a novelty yet it even has a little fan action and an energetic jam.  they've just "spent a month in the studio" indeed.
one of my favorites definitely a 5 star show.  how about the "they love each other"  every song is executed with perfection.

Sweet '73 Nothing better that a '73 from ol' Jerry Moore.  Highlights of the show, naturally, are the jams.  Best bets:  Bird Song, Playin', HCSS, Let it Grow,  and then, of course, the pinnacle is the entire segment from Truckin' through to Eyes.  Fantastic!

Great ending jam, otherwise not great The only thing preventing me from calling this show "overrated" is that the first set is excellent, though hardly unusual setlist-wise. I will say this show is definitely energetic, but musically most of it is awkward & directionless & not all that good. Furthermore Donna Jean is at her screechiest. I love '73 shows, but not this one. If you're looking to hear good music, stream the soundboard version of the first set. Excellent sound quality.

matrix dreams This is an excellent AUD, and I prefer AUDs actually. But how wonderful it would be to hear this recording paired with the SBD! 

Funny, what I would have done in the old days to get what is effectively a first generation recording.... How the IA spoils us!

Thanks to everyone who makes this cornucopia of aural bliss possible.
someone's bored Someone snores around 1:10 mark in Stella Blue! They even got their Me and My Uncle (or You and Your Sister) and still snored. Great show.
Favorite for personal reason I was there.
Eyes of the World This show contains a tremendous early Eyes of the World according to my opinion.
